<h2>Teaching (current)</h2>

<ul>
<li>INF6460 - Information Retrieval and Filtering
(Téluq, UQAM), to be offered in early 2007. This course is a solid
survey of Information Retrieval, from vector models to PageRank and
including collaborative filtering (in French).</li>

<li><a
href="http://v5o5jotqkgfu3btr91t7w5fhzedjaoaz8igl.unbsj.ca/~kaser/courses/OLAP-2006/">
CS6905 Advanced Technologies for E-Business</a> (2006 version)
(University of New Brunswick). In this graduate course, we cover OLAP and Data Warehousing with a research perspective.</li>

<li><a href="http://www.daniel-lemire.com/xml/">INF 6450 -
Information Management with XML (in French)</a> (<a
href="http://www.daniel-lemire.com/xml/guideetude/pdf/guidecourt.pdf">pdf</a>),
offered since January 2006 (Téluq, UQAM). The Firefox browser is necessary
to browse the course web site. Topics include DOM, DocBook, MathML, XSLT, SVG, XHTML, CSS, RDF, RSS.</li>


<li><a href="http://teluq.uqam.ca/expl_inf9002/"
rel="nofollow">INF 9002 - Evaluation and Analysis of Information
Systems (in French)</a>, course coordinator, (Téluq, UQAM). This course
is a business-oriented introduction to information systems.</li>
</ul>

